<h3 id="making-key-symbols">Making Key Symbols</h3>

<p>Because markdown can also accept html input, you can use the html keyboard
tag to create key symbols:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;kbd&gt;ESC&lt;/kbd&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>makes the symbol: <kbd>ESC</kbd>.</p>

<h3 id="using-unicode-characters">Using Unicode Characters</h3>

<p>You can specify unicode characters to be displayed in your Markdown
document. You must know the numberical HTML code. <a href="https://www.utf8-chartable.de/">This
Page</a> is my go-to reference for finding
these. Be sure to select <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">decimal</code> under <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">numerical HTML encoding of the
Unicode character</code> to get the correct code.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&amp;#10230;
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>produces a right facing arrow or ‚ü∂</p>
